  "title": "Customer Relations Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Lead Customer Relations Officer (HDB Project)</strong></p><p>We are an established construction firm looking for a <strong>Lead Customer Relations Officer (CRO)</strong> to manage\npublic relations for our ongoing HDB site. The candidate must be hands-on,firm, and capable of handling residents and authorities professionally.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Handle\n     Complaints:</strong> Resolve all conflicts, feedback, and complaints from\n     residents and shop tenants regarding the project.</li><li><strong>Meeting\n     Representative:</strong> Attend dialogue sessions and meetings with the <strong>Client,\n     RC, CCC, Town Council,</strong> and other government bodies.</li><li><strong>Ground\n     Engagement:</strong> Conduct regular house-to-house visits to residents\n     affected by the works. Update them on work schedules and any potential\n     impact (noise, dust, etc.).</li><li><strong>Reporting:</strong>\n     Keep proper records of all feedback and report to the Project\n     Manager/Board.</li><li><strong>Ad-hoc:</strong>\n     Any other public relations duties assigned by the management.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong>\n     Minimum GCE \"A\" Level or Diploma (any field).</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong>\n     At least <strong>2 years of experience</strong> in similar experience</li><li><strong>Industry:</strong>\n     Experience in <strong>HDB projects</strong> (HIP, BTO, or Lift Upgrading) is a major\n     advantage.</li><li><strong>Skills:</strong>\n     Must be able to communicate well with residents and handle difficult\n     situations on-site.</li><li><strong>Entry-Level:</strong>\n     Candidates with no experience but have at least GCE “O” Level may be\n     considered for the <strong>APRO (Assistant Public Relations Officer)</strong> role.</li></ul><p><strong>To Apply:</strong></p><p>Please apply with your resume with the following information:</p><ol><li><strong>Current & Expected Salary</strong></li><li><strong>Reason for Leaving</strong></li><li><strong>Availability / Notice Period</strong></li></ol><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</em></p><p><br /><br /></p>",
